					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>118 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>235</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>118 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each, marked with signatures at the beginning and at the end.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leaves individually guarded.</p>
									<p>Tidemarks and staining, mostly in margins.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="27" writtenLines="27">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words in larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Marginal notes.</p>
									<p>Ornaments along the last line of text, initial words, as well as around catchwords and running titles, in red ink. </p>
									<p>Maniculae (e.g., 24v).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Mosheh ben Yoshua Merkis</name>, inscribed in rhymed verses, folio 101v, 102r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Shelomoh Falk</name>: inscribed in rhymed verses, folio 101v, 102r.</p>
							<p>Folio 116r: entries of births in 1564, 1566, 1569 respectively, with an entry of death added in each case. Two others recording deaths follow.</p>
							<p>Folio 117v: short notes in Yiddish.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name> (active 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, 1623 (folio 115r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolomitano</name> (active 1575-1624): inscribed with his name, 1602 (folio 115v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Ma'aloth Ham-Middoth. Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harl. Or. 340.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
